  exerciseName: IfElseChain
  exerciseTitle: If Else Chain
  exerciseText: 'Write an if else chain that tests if the number is positive or negative
    or zero

    Call the functions inside the if: ExercisePositive(); ExerciseNegative();
    ExerciseZero();

'
  hintText: 'The syntax is if { } else if { } else { }

'
  solutionText: "if (number > 0) {\r\n    ExercisePositive();\r\n} else if (number
    < 0) {\r\n    ExerciseNegative();\r\n} else {\r\n    ExerciseZero();\r\n}"
  completedText: 'Here you learned to write a simple if else chain where you can
    write a condition and then write another if within the first if''s else.

'
